cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper is about semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a neural network architecture, which involves training and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of global inference for semantic segmentation, which involves higher-level understanding of image content, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. The paper also involves natural language processing techniques, such as labeling and classification, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the proposed method on standard datasets, which involves benchmarking and performance analysis, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category.
